metadata.name: Pine trees in the cold #11
metadata.description:
Pine and cypress trees were originally trees growing in cold zones and mountains. Due to their long-term life in cold environment, they have formed a unique cold resistant structure. The leaves of pine and cypress trees are generally reduced in needle shape, linear or scale shape. Due to the small leaf area, water is not easy to evaporate and lose. Some leaves have thick cutin or wax, and some have thick villi. If you take a pine needle and observe it carefully, you can see that there are dense white fluff on it, which feels very smooth when touching,

This is the picture of pine and cypress in the cold winter

metadata.name: Hall of Mirrors #91
metadata.description:
The Hall of Mirrors, a 3D installation using vertex shader and digital feedback.
Inspired by Kraftwerk's song and old house of mirrors funfair attractions from my childhood.

Instructions:
- use the mouse to navigate (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'b' to play/pause the animation
- press 'p' to download the current view it in a custom resolution (only in live view).

Berlin, December 2021
@bgola

Traditional haikus consist of 3 phrases that contain 17 syllables in a 5, 7, 5 pattern and a¬†kigo : a seasonal or time reference. This generated artwork draws on the aesthetic of lo-fi punk  to create a series of unique poems, digitally animated to bring out the violence of the 80s counterculture in opposition to the sweet poetry of traditional haikus.

metadata.name: Elasticity #25
metadata.description:
Elasticity is a collection that explores the ambiguity of discrete continuity in architecture.

Elasticity is a tectonic, generative system that combines simple, discrete parts into an elastic relationship between part and whole, creating a discrete and continuous elastic form. A form that celebrates the continuity of digital variation while respecting a discrete approach to a digital whole.

It is a generative follow-up to the project CM.CollabWood, where the same parts were embedded in a real-time participatory architectural environment, where clusters of parts were placed by participants in real-time in collective design sessions to create tangible collective open forms.

___________________________________________________
Controls:
‚Ä¢ 'P' pause/play animation
‚Ä¢ 'B' monochrome mode (wait a bit for recalculation)

Resize Canvas in live/open mode:
(press once and wait for recalculation!)
‚Ä¢ 'DoubleClick' go Fullscreen
‚Ä¢ '1' square 1024x1024
‚Ä¢ '2' square 2048x2048
‚Ä¢ '3' square 3072x3072
‚Ä¢ '4' square 4096x4096 (might not work on all laptops)
‚Ä¢ '5' landscape 4000x3000
‚Ä¢ '6' portrait 3000x4000
‚Ä¢ '7' fullHD 1920x1080
‚Ä¢ '8' UHD 3840 x 2160
‚Ä¢ '9' square small(for sharing a gif on twitter) 512x512
‚Ä¢ '0' flex. adapt to current window size

Save & Export in live/open mode:
‚Ä¢ 's' save a .png of in current resolution
‚Ä¢ 'g' save a seamless loop .gif in current resolution
(press the key and wait for export, might take some time, consider with higher resolutions files get pretty big)

Steps to save a gif/png :
‚Ä¢ go in live/open mode (wait)
‚Ä¢ resize canvas to your desired resolution (wait)
‚Ä¢ press s or g and wait for recalculation & download to finish
‚Ä¢ enjoy elasticity :)
___________________________________________________


This token may not work on mobile(!), but it allows exporting .png and .gif (see controls) to enjoy elasticity on different displays or mobile. Tested on Mozilla, Chrome, Safari. Created with P5js & p5.createLoop

Elasticity Generative Token by @grasser_alex 2022
